        "generateUrl": "https://clerk.happenstance.ai/oauth/register",
        "setup": "For MCP clients that self-onboard with OAuth, register a client via [dynamic client registration](https://clerk.happenstance.ai/oauth/register). The service's OAuth flow uses authorization at [`https://happenstance.ai/oauth/authorize`](https://happenstance.ai/oauth/authorize) and token exchange at [`https://clerk.happenstance.ai/oauth/token`](https://clerk.happenstance.ai/oauth/token). Available scopes include `profile`, `email`, `public_metadata`, `private_metadata`, `offline_access`, and `user:org:read`. In practice, MCP-compatible clients can usually initiate this flow automatically when connecting to the MCP server.",
